      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "BROTHER SAM (4) sat on speed and lifted strongly to open winning account two back, then finished a 1.3 lengths fourth last start at Capalaba over 366m (19.96). Returns to the scene of his maiden win. This looks easier and expected to bounce back. REGAL MALT (1) returned a better run last time, finishing in the money (19.64) at this track behind Menacing Mirage in a Grade 6. Has the early speed to land on the pace and can stick on. Safe beginner who draws ideally on the inside. Can measure up. SMASHING DOUBLE (2) finished third (17.01) two back at this track but out of the placings last time when 6th there. Key player if finds best. VITESSE ETOILE (7) is worth consideration.",
